{"title":"Cyclist Track Days bikes #27: Ribble Allroad Ti","link":"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/cyclist-track-days-bikes-ribble-allroad-ti","date":1745401895000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/cyclist-track-days-bikes-ribble-allroad-ti\">Cyclist Track Days bikes #27: Ribble Allroad Ti</a></p>\n\n<p>It’s almost time to kick off our 2025 <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/cyclist-track-days-information\">Cyclist Track Days</a> events, where you can test the latest top-end bikes from the leading brands on the market. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>The last (maybe, maybe not) bike added to our <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/bikes-cyclist-track-days-2025\">amazing lineup</a> of the ones that you can test ride at this years Track Days is the Ribble Allroad Ti.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The Ribble Allroad Ti does what it says on the tin: it’s Ribble titanium all-road bike. It’s a recent addition to the British brand’s lineup alongside the carbon <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/reviews/ribble-allroad-sl-r-road-bike-review\">Allroad SL R</a>, which you will also find at Track Days. <em>Cyclist</em> writer Mike Anderson recently reviewed it and described it as a ‘versatile, easy-to-ride machine that thanks to its stunning titanium finish and associated ride quality is easy to like as well’.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Read Mike’s full review <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/reviews/ribble-allroad-ti-road-bike-review\">here</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The Ribble Allroad Ti will be at the following Track Days events:</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>26<sup>th</sup> April 2025, Odd Down Cycle Track Bath,<br />17<sup>th</sup> May 2025, Lee Valley VeloPark London,<br />7<sup>th</sup> June 2025, The Brownlee Centre, Leeds</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>For more information on Cyclist Track Days click <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/cyclist-track-days-information\">here</a>.</p>\n\n\n<div>\r\n                <div>\r\n                   <div>\r\n     